AMERICAN writer Scott Westerfeld once said: “You young things are too easily persuaded by the touch of lips.” According to the young fiction writer, there is great power in one’s lips and all it takes is a little touch. Scott highlights the power of the lips and lips like one’s personality often tend to inform others of the kind of person you are. According to Readers Digest, if eyes are a window to the soul, then the lips may just be a framework to our character. This, according to face scientists around the world, is one way to tell what type of personality one has.This is all in the type of lips one has. Experts further suggest the shape of your lips may signify even deeper psychological peculiarities and personality traits. So, what type of lips do you have and what do they say about your personality? Readers Digest gives us the breakdown: 1. N
  aturally Full Lip
 
 s Evenly and naturally plump on both top and bottom, this lip shape indicates that you are an empathetic individual with strong parenting instincts. People with this lip shape harbour an innate desire to safeguard and protect others. Their caring and selfless nature means they deeply care about others and find great pleasure in doing so. 2. Thin Top and Bottom Lips Women with thin lips tend to be loners and rather timid. Their introverted personality also means they are self-reliant. They are fine with being alone and are perfectly content with the idea of being independent. 3. Lips That Are Plumper in the Centre People with a plump lip centre revel in the spotlight and pride themselves on being natural performers. They prefer to surround themselves with people rather than being alone. 4. Lips With a Peaked Cupid’s Bow People with a peaked cupid’s bow are defined by their creativity. They constantly strive for self-expression in every form, with productive, artistic results. They’re also very self-aware and have impressive memory recall abilities.